-- S.Korea Samsung Heavy says wins $600 mln ship order
-- 
-- Sun Jul 1, 2007 8:00pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/07/02/us-samsungheavy-order-idUSSEO3809920070702

 

 SEOUL  (Reuters) - South Korea's Samsung Heavy Industries Co. ( 010140.KS ), said on Monday it had won an order worth about $600 million to build a drillship for a company in the Americas. 

 "We won the deal over the weekend," a Samsung Heavy spokesman said by telephone. On Friday, Samsung said it had secured a 551.4 billion won ($597.1 million) order to build a drillship for a different company in the Americas.